@startuml

!include ../theme.puml

title RecallRadar - Revision Lifecycle

actor User

participant "Topic"
participant "RevisionService"
participant "RevisionLog"
participant "LeakScoreService"
participant "TopicMetrics"
participant "AnalyticsService"

User -> Topic : Study Topic

User -> RevisionService : Log Revision

RevisionService -> RevisionLog : Create Revision Entry

RevisionLog --> RevisionService : Saved

RevisionService -> LeakScoreService : Recalculate Metrics

LeakScoreService -> TopicMetrics : Update Scores

TopicMetrics --> LeakScoreService : Saved

LeakScoreService --> RevisionService : Updated

RevisionService --> User : Revision Recorded

User -> AnalyticsService : Request Due Topics

AnalyticsService -> TopicMetrics : Evaluate Priorities

TopicMetrics --> AnalyticsService : Scores

AnalyticsService --> User : Due Topics List

note right

Business Rules

1. Every revision creates
   a RevisionLog.

2. Revision history is never
   overwritten.

3. Metrics are derived from
   RevisionLog data.

4. Topics with higher leak
   scores receive higher
   revision priority.

end note

@enduml